title: For Sale:  Winchester 1885 Schuetzen Hi Wall 32-40 - 38A Tang Sight & Excellent Bore
postcontent: Offered for your consideration is this beautiful 1885 Schuetzen Hi Wall in 32-40 caliber. Made in 1889 it has a 30 inch #3 octagon barrel. The bore is excellent, the rifling is bright and sharp from muzzle to chamber with zero throat erosion. I rate the bore condition a strong 9++ on a 1 to 10 scale, it will be an excellent shooter! The barrel retains 60%+ blue with traces of dark plum. There is wear to sharp edges and carry wear forward of the receiver. The front sight is a Winchester #67A Globe with fine "A" bead insert. The rear is a Winchester #22B with serrated edges and correct elevator. The receiver retains 30 to 40% faded case colors and has a Winchester #38A Mid Range tang sight mounted. The tang sight is intact and operates smoothly with no wobble in firing position. The elevation graduations are sharp and clean. There are traces of blue but mostly a plum gray patina. Mechanically the receiver is excellent, cocks properly on closing, half and full cock hold properly. The trigger break is crisp at 3 pounds. The wood is excellent and stands proud above the metal in all mating areas of the forend, receiver and buttplate. It shows no evidence of ever being sanded or refinished and I believe the finish to be original factory varnish. There is one small chip at the toe of the buttplate. There are numerous light handling marks that were obviously made long ago but I see no cracks or chips other than the one at the toe of the buttstock. The nickel plating on the Swiss buttplate has either worn off or been removed. I see traces of plating but it's mostly brass finish. The buttstock has had weight added and apparently set up as an off hand rifle. Weight is 12.3 pounds. The Cody Museum letter lists the serial number date 8-21-1889, date shipped 8-2-1890 under order #15477. Caliber is 32-40 with #3 octagon barrel and plain trigger. This is a fine vintage Schuetzen style Winchester that is an antique and can be shipped direct. I'll be glad to provide additional photos, just send your email address and the specific views you would like to see.

title: For Trade:  Don't get ripped off, check the retail price before you buy used!!!
postcontent:
A lot of people are asking more for used guns than you would pay at a gun shop.  
Before you buy a used gun, check the value at  your local gun shop or on gunbroker.com for guns with actual bids.
This will give you an idea of the guns real value, not some idiots inflated value.  
For example, a high point for $400 dollars, these retail for under $200.
Glocks for $700, these retail for under $600.

title: For Sale:  LaRue Tactical PredatAR 16" Upper
postcontent:
PredatAR 5.56 Overview
The PredatAR 5.56 is designed for those who are searching for a lightweight, ultra-reliable and accurate 5.56 mm NATO rifle for home-defense, competition-shooting or hunting. The PredatAR takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 “Lite” design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. By contouring the barrel, skeletonizing the handguard, lowering and simplifying the upper rail, and using a low-profile gas block, we were able to reduce roughly 2 pounds from the standard OBR 5.56 rifle.
The barrels are Stainless Steel, lightweight-profiled, Wylde chambered and feature polygonal rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in ½ x 28, with an A2 flash hider attached* (other muzzle devices can be added at an additional cost).
The handguards on the PredatAR extend out 14.75”, to suit a larger range of shooting styles. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet 7075-T6, for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though we lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy.
XTRAXN™ is a proprietary chamber feature added to reduce frictional forces caused by pressure-expanded cartridge cases bearing against chamber walls. Facilitates reliable extraction through a wide range of temperature / chamber pressure extremes. XTRAXN™ extends extractor life, while having no effect on the firearm's accuracy. All this, and it dovetails well with the OBR's world-famous accuracy.
Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO
Barrel Length: 16.1“

Muzzle Thread Configuration: ½ x 28 *

Gas System: Mid-Length Direct Impingement
